parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Sending Unit Gasket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank sending unit gasket can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to hazardous conditions, fires, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel tank
fuel pours out of the tank when making a right turn
fuel gauge does not register the proper amount
fuel tank cracks
and gas spills out of the hole.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel rail can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to hazardous conditions, fires, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel rail
fuel spray near the exhaust manifold
and fuel rail failure at the factory-installed plugged end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to hazardous conditions, fires, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel tank
fuel pours out of the tank
and the tank cracks on the right lower corner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to accidents or stranding.
symptoms: Fuel gauge does not register the proper amount
vehicle runs out of fuel even though the fuel gauge registers a quarter of a tank left
and gas gauge failed.
